Liquidity and Capital Resources
Our principal sources of liquidity are our cash and cash equivalents and cash generated from operations, proceeds from issuance of
debt, financing leases, the sale of certain receivables and the Revolving Credit Facility (as defined below). Further, the incurrence
of additional indebtedness may inhibit our ability to incur new debt in the future to finance our business strategy under the terms
governing our existing and future indebtedness.
