Senior Secured Notes
Following the achievement of an investment grade issuer rating from each of the three main credit rating agencies, on August 22,
2022, we entered into an amendment (“Credit Agreement Amendment”) to our Credit Agreement, dated April 1, 2020 to release the
liens securing the obligations under the Credit Agreement. Upon effectiveness of the Credit Agreement Amendment, the liens
securing the Senior Secured Notes were also automatically released, and our obligations under the Senior Secured Notes (thereafter,
together with our other senior unsecured notes, “Senior Notes”), which for the avoidance of doubt exclude the Spectrum-Backed
Notes, are no longer secured.
Senior Notes
The Senior Notes are guaranteed on a senior unsecured basis by the Company and certain of our consolidated subsidiaries. They are
redeemable at our discretion, in whole or in part, at any time. The redemption price is calculated by reference to date on which such
notes are redeemed and generally includes a premium that steps down gradually as the Senior Notes approach their par call date, on
or after which they are redeemable at par. The amount of time by which the par call date precedes the maturity date of the
respective series of Senior Notes varies from one to three years.
